race.comment: Despite the weight the honest REVANTAS (1) looks hard to beat. Runner-up here before a break making it three minors from four tries. Tilley aboard and drawn well. Expected to go close fresh. BRAVE LIKE LILY (9) made debut here over 1000m when strode forward and sat second and run over late, finishing fourth. Better for it and despite a tricky gate should run well. ZOUSAIN GIRL (17) has been freshened since a below-par run last time here over 1200m. Best figure stack right up to this field and worth another chance.  KACHINA GIRL (14) is overdue for a win and looks well weighted here with the claim. Drawn for a good run with cover and should be winding up late. SPLASH LUMA (6) is a filly by Yes Yes Yes on debut. Has looked good in two trials leading into this and makes debut on home track. Watch closely for a move.
